{"id":14881080,"mediaExerciseId":"c3a4c450-5a07-4a53-a855-217f28b67b8d","exerciseName":"31","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":236,"solutions":[{"id":6022534,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should find the amount of the deposit that we need to pay each year from now on, to have 2.5 million dollars on our account at 40 years old.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/7973ec6399ff1b8830e89294064cf92b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/7973ec6399ff1b8830e89294064cf92b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"First, we have to find the real rate, and then we should calculate an annuity.\n\nTo calculate the exact real rate, we will use the Fisher effect. The Fisher effect tells us the correlation between the nominal return, real return, and rising prices(inflation). Investors are always willing to invest in a security with a positive actual return. The only way for the investor to invest in the negative return of a bond will be in the time of deflation. The formula for the Fisher effect is as follows:\n\n$$1+\\text{R}=\\left(1+\\text{r}\\right)\\times\\left(1+\\text{h}\\right)$$\n\nR- the nominal return\n\nr- the real return\n\nh- inflation effect","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":455,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/8ab44108e24cf75339e13a0d4097d140/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":229,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/8ab44108e24cf75339e13a0d4097d140/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's calculate the real rate.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{r}&=\\dfrac{1+10.3\\%}{1+3.7\\%}-1\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\dfrac{1.103}{1.037}-1\\\\[15pt]\n&=0.063645\\times100\\\\[15pt]\n&=6.36\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe real rate of return is 6.36\\%.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":465,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/d3378bc0704e431f73ec5635a468a455/lateximg_large.png","width":621},"regular":{"height":234,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/d3378bc0704e431f73ec5635a468a455/lateximg.png","width":311}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we should calculate the annuity that we have to pay each year to reach our goal.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Future value}=&\\text{Annuity}\\times\\dfrac{\\left(1+\\text{real rate}\\right)^\\text{n-1}}{\\text{real rate}}\\\\[15pt]\n\\$2.5\\text{mio}=&\\text{Annuity}\\times\\dfrac{\\left(1+6.36\\%\\right)^{39}}{6.36\\%}\\\\[15pt]\n\\text{Annuity}=&\\dfrac{\\$2.5\\text {mio}}{174.344}\\\\[15pt]\n\\text{Annuity}=&\\$14,342.73\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\n**To reach our goal, we should pay each year \\$14,342.73.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":550,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/b5c79266baf27b5595ceb33d36a8e880/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":276,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/22e41cc37f92b4c65ec8fdfd9c612a49/b5c79266baf27b5595ceb33d36a8e880/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"7895f9ee-d929-47dd-9342-5deda0c1684a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":n